-- Poland extends flat rate guidance until at least end-Q3 2014
-- By Karolina Slowikowska
-- Wed Mar 05, 2014 10:05AM EST
-- None



WARSAW, March 5 (Reuters) - Poland's central bank extended its guidance on Wednesday, saying interest rates will likely remain at their all-time low of 2.5 percent until at least the end of September 2014, the bank said in a statement.

"Rates should stay unchanged in the longer term, that is at least until the end of the third quarter, " the bank said in a statement.